I'll calculate the requested financial ratios based on the provided financial statements. Let me work through each ratio step by step.

## Current Ratio
Current Ratio = Total Current Assets / Total Current Liabilities
= $29,413,723.95 / $8,028,630.43
= 3.66

## Quick Ratio
Quick Ratio = (Current Assets - Inventory) / Current Liabilities
= ($29,413,723.95 - $7,400,000.00) / $8,028,630.43
= $22,013,723.95 / $8,028,630.43
= 2.74

## Debt to Asset Ratio
Debt to Asset Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Assets
= $8,028,630.43 / $39,772,748.32
= 0.20

## Debt to Equity Ratio
Debt to Equity Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Owner's Equity
= $8,028,630.43 / $31,744,117.89
= 0.25

## Cash Flow to Debt Ratio
Cash Flow to Debt Ratio = Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities / Total Liabilities
= -$10,442,735.47 / $8,028,630.43
= -1.30
